Peel and cut vegetables into 3-inch julienne strips. In a large saucepan combine vegetables, water and apple juice, cover, cook until tender (45 - 55 minutes). Drain. Add butter, honey, thyme, nutmeg and pepper to saucepan, melt butter and honey over medium heat. Return vegetables to the saucepan and cook over medium heat, uncovered, stirring until glazed, about 6 minutes.